abstract.text: struct defines a SwiftUI view that allows users to select a reason for not enabling TouchID on their macOS device. Declination reasons are shuffled before being presented in order to remove proximty bias in the results (the tendency for end-users to favor options towards the middle of a list). Declination reasons are defined in outside this view in the

enum defines various reasons why a user might decline to enable TouchID on their macOS device. Each case represents a specific reason and includes a description that provides more details about the reason. This enum conforms to the
protocols, enabling easy iteration, identification, and string representation of each reason.
